Here is a simple for loop in C# that prints all numbers from 0 to 10 that are divisible by 2:

```csharp
for(int i = 0; i <= 10; i++)
{
    if(i % 2 == 0)
    {
        Console.WriteLine(i);
    }
}
```

This program works by iterating over the numbers from 0 to 10 using a for loop. For each number, it checks if the number is divisible by 2 by using the modulus operator `%`. If the remainder is 0, then the number is divisible by 2 and it is printed to the console.
